Description. Measurements. Medium-sized individuals; crown 1.5– 4 mm long; 5–8 pairs of radioles, number of radioles often different in left and right halves of crown (
Table 3
). Complete specimens with trunk 2.5– 7 mm long, 0.4–0.75 mm wide; 4–5 thoracic and 21 –~ 50 abdominal chaetigers, often with different numbers of thoracic chaetigers in left and right sides of body (
Table 3
